-- Holcim CEO Has to Close Plants, Cut Costs, SonntagsZeitung Says
-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 2012-04-01T11:08:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-01/holcim-ceo-has-to-close-plants-cut-costs-sonntagszeitung-says.html
Bernard Fontana,  Holcim Ltd. (HOLN) ’s new
chief executive officer, will have to restructure the cement
maker’s business in  Europe  where additional plants will have to
be closed, cut costs, and expand the company’s business in
 emerging markets ,  SonntagsZeitung  said, citing criteria set for
him by the board of directors.  Details of Fontana’s plans will be presented on April 17 at
the company’s shareholder meeting, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Richard Weiss  in Frankfurt at 
